---
import CaseStudy from '../../layouts/CaseStudy.astro';
---

<CaseStudy
  title="The LAB Miami — CWK. Work"
  description="How CWK helped The LAB Miami build clear positioning, content infrastructure, and team alignment as the foundation for its next chapter."
  category="Builder Hub"
  client="The LAB Miami"
  headline="The LAB Miami Builds the Foundation for Its Next Chapter With CWK."
  result="30%"
  resultLabel="Faster sales cycles"
>

  <!-- Stats row -->
  <div class="cs-stats">
    <div class="cs-stat">
      <span class="cs-stat-num">30%</span>
      <span class="cs-stat-label">Faster Sales Cycles</span>
    </div>
    <div class="cs-stat">
      <span class="cs-stat-num">50%</span>
      <span class="cs-stat-label">Faster Content Creation</span>
    </div>
    <div class="cs-stat">
      <span class="cs-stat-num">Team</span>
      <span class="cs-stat-label">Alignment Achieved</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Location callout -->
  <div class="glass-card" style="padding: 28px 32px;">
    <p style="font-size: 13px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; color: var(--dim); margin-bottom: 8px;">Location</p>
    <p style="font-size: 20px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--text); margin-bottom: 8px;">Wynwood, Miami</p>
    <p style="margin: 0;">Builder Hub for founders, technologists, investors, and creators</p>
  </div>

  <!-- More Than Just Content -->
  <div class="cs-section">
    <h2>More Than Just Content</h2>
    <p>
      Over the past few months, The LAB Miami has been quietly doing the work most brands skip:
      building infrastructure before scaling visibility.
    </p>
    <p>
      What began as a fast-moving request to produce social media content turned into something
      more strategic. Instead of producing one-off videos, the focus shifted to clarity, systems,
      and long-term brand foundation.
    </p>
    <p>
      Our work together introduced a clear signal: this is a campus built for serious builders.
      Short scenes, real people, and the energy of the space were used to create familiarity
      and credibility — not just hype.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- Clear Positioning -->
  <div class="cs-section">
    <h2>Clear Positioning</h2>
    <p>
      Through synthesis and messaging work, the LAB's direction was sharpened into three
      defining pillars:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>A globally connected innovation campus</li>
      <li>Rooted in Wynwood</li>
      <li>Built for founders, technologists, investors, and creators</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      This clarity now guides future content, partnerships, and programming.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- Content as Infrastructure -->
  <div class="cs-section">
    <h2>Content as Infrastructure</h2>
    <p>
      Rather than scattered posts, the work focused on creating reusable, editorial-style content.
      Assets were built to support multiple campaigns, future announcements, and long-term
      visibility — reducing the need to constantly start from scratch.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- Closing quote -->
  <div class="glass-card" style="padding: 32px; border-left: 3px solid var(--cyan);">
    <p style="font-size: 18px; font-style: italic; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--text); margin: 0;">
      "We don't just produce content, events, and workshops... we orchestrate perception
      in alignment with your true impact."
    </p>
  </div>

</CaseStudy>
